

# EmotionServer
## Build instructions

create a new GCP VM instance running Debian / GNU Linux and standard config

sudo apt-get install pip git

sudo apt-get install python3-pip

sudo apt-get install graphviz

sudo pip3 install virtualenv

sudo apt-get install python3-venv

sudo apt-get install python-scipy

sudo apt-get install nginx

pip install wheel

pip install keras

pip install tensorflow

pip install opencv-python

pip install sklearn

pip install imageio

pip install Flask

python3 -m venv EmotionEnvironment

source EmotionEnvironment/bin/activate

git clone https://github.com/thoughtworksarts/EmoPy.git

cd EmoPy

pip3 install -r requirements.txt 

sudo pip3 install opencv-python

edit ./EmoPy/EmoPy/src/data_generator.py
  on line 5: K.set_image_dim_ordering('th') --> K.set_image_data_format('channels_last')

from ./EmoPy
  mv EmoPy ../EmotionEnvironment/lib/python3.7/site-packages/

edit /EmotionEnvironment/lib/python3.7/site-packages/EmoPy/src/fermodel.py
  add: import imageio
  change: misc.imread --> imageio.imread

configure nginx on port 80 to proxy to Flask server running on localhost:5000

modify predict_from_ndarray() function in fermodel.py on line 70 to return full prediction array instead of single dominant expression
  

# Run the server:

source EmotionEnvironment/bin/activate

nohup python3 EmotionServer/server.py & 



# API documentation

POST to /image

 request content type:
 "application/json"  

 request body:
 {"image":"data-uri"}

 response body:
 {
 "happy": 0.46,
 "angry": 0.54
}

# Sample CURL request

curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"image":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"}' http://35.236.114.44/image
